headline.main: WAR WITH AUSTRALIA BLOW TO TOKYO ENVOY; Kawai Stressed Unhappiness When He Sailed for Home

lead_paragraph: MELBOURNE, Australia, Sept. 2 -- "I have failed in my mission and I am returning to Japan a bitterly disappointed man," said the former Japanese Minister, Tatsuo Kawai, who left Australia Aug. 16 bound for Lourenco Marques, Portuguese East Africa, on an exchange ship.
abstract: Jap Min to Australia T Kawai deplores Japan-Australian relations; urges white races post-war cooperation with Asiatics
